  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a successor algebra; <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CR.xml"
addr="jms-00CR"
title="Lifting homomorphisms to the induced successor algebra">we have shown</fr:link> that weak algebra homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{I}\xrightarrow {{\iota }}{s\cdot X}]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> to the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CC.xml"
addr="jms-00CC"
title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> also tracks a successor algebra homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\bar {I}}\xrightarrow {{\iota }}{X}]]></fr:tex>. To see that this homomorphism is <fr:em>unique</fr:em>, fix any <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CA.xml"
addr="jms-00CA"
title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\bar {I}}\xrightarrow {{j}}{X}]]></fr:tex>; we <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00D9.xml"
addr="jms-00D9"
title="From successor algebra homomorphisms to weak algebra homomorphisms">have also shown</fr:link> that such a homomorphism also tracks a (<fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00C8.xml"
addr="jms-00C8"
title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</fr:link>) homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{I}\xrightarrow {{j}}{s\cdot X}]]></fr:tex>. But <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{I}\xrightarrow {{\iota }}{s\cdot X}]]></fr:tex> is the such weak algebra homomorphism, so we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\iota  = j]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
