title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> be the initial weak algebra for a monad <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {T}]]></fr:tex> on a category <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>. Then the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CN.xml"
addr="jms-00CN"
title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {I}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:em>initial</fr:em> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00C9.xml"
addr="jms-00C9"
title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</fr:link> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {T}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
